      • secureApply

        protected static <T> Optional<T> secureApply(T _val1,
                                             T _val2,
                                             BiFunction<T,T,T> _function)
        Applies to the given function the two given values but never applies if any of them is null
        • if _val1 and _val2 are null: return Empty optional
        • if _val1 or _val2 are null: return an optional of the not null value
        • if _val1 and _val2 are not null: return Optional of _function.apply(_val1,_val2)
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the values to apply
        Parameters:
        _val1 - first value to apply _function
        _val2 - second value to apply _function
        _function - funtion to apply returning the same type
        Returns:
        Optional.empty (if both values are null), Optional.of(_function.apply(_val1,_val2)) (if both of them are not null) and Optional.of(one of not null _val1 or _val2) (if any of them is null)
        See Also:
        Optional, BiFunction
